CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1962, pg. 24, reads: "New Faces With Pirates - These are some of the new faces found among the 1962 Pittsburgh Pirates.  At left is outfielder - first baseman Donn Clendenon, who will take over in left field if Bob Skinner flunks out again...  No rookie figured in Tuesday's opening day, 6-0 scuttling of the Phillies, but Veale was named to start the second game.  Only very impressive rookies get early calls of that sort,"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Pittsburgh Pirates baseball player Donn Clendenon, holding glove on Forbes Field
